YesBoth is a digital tool for interpersonal communication assistance enabling consenting adults to generate messages structuring their consent agreements.

The Application operates exclusively client-side (browser). No data entered is transmitted to a server, collected, stored, analyzed, or monetized.

The Application does NOT constitute:
— a legal or legal aid service;
— a contract, authentic deed, or private deed with evidentiary value;
— evidence under civil law;
— a substitute for verbal, gestural, or physical consent.

MESSAGES GENERATED BY THE APPLICATION HAVE NO LEGALLY BINDING VALUE.

Messages produced by YesBoth:
— do not constitute contracts;
— carry no presumption of validity or authenticity;
— cannot be invoked as evidence before any court;
— cannot override public order provisions on consent, particularly criminal law.

Verbal, gestural, or physical consent ALWAYS prevails over any written document. Refusal expressed in any form, at any time, is absolutely binding and immediately irrevocable, notwithstanding any prior agreement.

Silence, passivity, or absence of physical resistance does not constitute consent under the law.

EXTENDED DISCLAIMER

6.1 — Exclusive user responsibility
The user is solely and fully responsible for:
— their use of the Application and generated messages;
— the accuracy of information entered;
— acts performed in connection with use of the Application;
— respect for the physical and moral integrity of any person involved;
— compliance with applicable laws.

6.2 — Total exclusion of Publisher liability
Herrichain EXCLUDES ALL LIABILITY for:
— any physical, moral, or material damage linked to use of the Application;
— any criminal offense committed by a user;
— any civil dispute between users;
— any misuse, fraudulent or unlawful use;
— any error or inaccuracy in generated messages;
— unavailability or malfunction of the Application.

6.3 — Exclusion of Developer liability
Artean Digital, as development service provider, is in no way responsible for user use of the Application. Its liability is strictly limited to its contractual obligations to the Publisher.

6.4 — Force majeure
Neither the Publisher nor the Developer can be held liable in cases of force majeure.

It is strictly prohibited to use the Application to:
— coerce, manipulate, or pressure any person to obtain their consent;
— represent a generated message as a legally binding commitment;
— impersonate a third party in input fields;
— use the Application for any commercial, professional, or lucrative purpose;
— commit or facilitate any criminal offense;
— access the Application as a minor.

Any breach solely engages the user's civil and criminal liability.
